::: image/src/RasterImage.cpp
@@ +558,5 @@
>      // Wait until the next refresh driver tick and try again
>      return false;
>    }
>  
> +  if (timeout < 0) {

This can actually never happen, because timeout is unsigned. I suspect that if you said timeout == 0, you might be closer to what you're looking for, though.

comments.text:
I think joe's suggesting replacing the current code's
  if (!(timeout > 0)) {
with
  if (timeout == 0) {
because those two statements are logically equivalent, given that "timeout" is unsigned.

